
function dts_command_source_invoke
{

pod2text << UNTIL_HERE

=pod

=head1 DATASET ($DTS_DATASET_ID)

The dataset is contained in a zip file, which should be manually downloaded. 

=head1 LINK

Will be made available through Code Ocean, or github. 

  Current link, status: $DTS_URI_PREREQ_EXAMPLE_DATASET_SOURCE
  
=head1 PREREQUISITES

You can manully download the files. However, alterantively you can download them from the commandline. On Ubuntu, you can use following commands to install these tools:

  $ sudo apt install wget

  # or
  
  $ sudo apt install curl

=head1 TARGET DIR

Please download the B<${DTS_DATASET_TARGET_FILENAME}> and unzip manullay into B<$DTS_DIR/data>.

=head1 INSTRUCTIONS

=head2 STEP1: DOWNLOAD REMOTE FILE

Typically, you can use any of these methods:

  $ wget https://.../${DTS_DATASET_TARGET_FILENAME}

  # or
  
  $ curl https://.../${DTS_DATASET_TARGET_FILENAME}

=head2 STEP2: UNPACK INTO TARGET DIR

Once the file is succesfully downloaded, use the B<unzip> command in your terminal:

 $ unzip ${DTS_DATASET_TARGET_FILENAME} -d $DTS_DIR/data

=head1 AUTHOR

Murat Uenalan <murat.uenalan@uni-konstanz.de>

=cut

UNTIL_HERE

}
